<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="11" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.0012/532r</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d11fn1">The same to the Ambassadors in Germany,
                                Austria-Hungary, and Russia.</note>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-15">
                                <hi rend="italic">September 15, 1914</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>We have just signed treaties with Great Britain, France, Spain and
                                China.<note n="2" xml:id="d11fn2">See <ref target="frus1914#pg_304">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1914, p. 304</ref>;
                                    <ref target="frus1915#pg_380">1915, p. 380</ref>; <ref target="frus1914#pg_1082">1914, p. 1082</ref>; <ref target="frus1915#pg_41">1915, p. 41</ref>.</note> These with the
                            twenty-two previously signed connect this Government with more than two
                            thirds of the population of the globe by peace treaties which provide
                            for investigation in all cases before hostilities can be commenced.
                            Please say to the sovereign to whom you are accredited that this
                            Government will be pleased to make a similar treaty with him.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>